Weather temperatures are expected to drop across the country from Thursday going to the weekend with the cold front expected in most parts of the country. In the Western Cape, the cold front is also expected to start on Thursday. Weather Forecaster, Venetia Phakula has advised people to stay indoors over the weekend as thunder showers are also expected. “Over the central parts of the country as the cold front enters the country we expect this air to start push in on Saturday over most parts of the central parts of the country that would include Gauteng. By Saturday we expect temperatures to drop significantly over the central parts of the country. And the recovery is happening on Sunday.” About Ditaba Tsotetsi View all posts by Ditaba Tsotetsi